reviewText: Dudley Boyz vs Rey Mysterio & Rob Van Dam: This match looked good on paper. When Van Dam started off, it was slow and really boring. I dont know why, RVD is one of my favorite wrestlers. Mysterio was tagged in and the match took off. A pretty good match overall. Mysterio and Van Dam was a dream team that never took off.Kurt Angle cuts a promo. I enjoyed his promos better when he had hair. Ever since he lost his hair, he lost his humour it seems.Torrie VS Dawn Marie: If Torrie lost, she'd be fired. Guess who wins.Mordecai vs Scotty 2 Hotty: I like jobber matches, just not on PPV's. Hard to believe Mordecai would be turned into Kevin Thorn a few years later.Charlie Haas & Rico vs Billy Gunn & Hardcore Holly: Two men who never got there due (besides a tag title run) battle two tag team specialist. Ho-hum match.Jacqueline vs Chavo Guerrero(with 1 hand tied behind his back)- WWE never got the concept of the crusierweight division. If I was in the crowd, i'd be wanting a refund.John Cena vs Rene Dupree: Cena in his Vanilla Ice phase. The match was decent but I did like the ending.Booker T vs Undertaker: Never liked Booker T. His claim of 5 time world champion should not even count. The WCW world title was being passed around like a hooker and anyone could have held it. The match was decent but the back story was better.Eddie Guerrero vs John Bradshaw Layfield-Loved the story of this match and the promo JBL cuts before this fight. Guerrerro bleeds like crazy and so does JBL. I hated the DQ finish, considering both men were bleeding like crazy.Overall, a decent event. The main event is worth seeing but the rest of the card was decent.

reviewText: I can't for the life of me, figure out why people hated this event as much as they did. Now don't get me wrong, this event wasn't exactly a stellar one either, but it was FAR better then people give it credit for.Dawn Marie v. Torrie Wilson- absolutely terrible. Except Dawn Marie's full moon. 1/10Tag Team championshipHaas/Rico v. Gunn/Holly- um, entertaining.. wrestling lacked a bit in this one but it was entertaining so I can't completely knock it. 4/10Mordecai v. Scotty 2 Hotty- Mordecai is SO green. That and the kid has stage fright like you wouldn't believe. nothing to get excited about. 3/10RVD and Rey Mysterio v. The Dudley Boyz- Expected a little better from these guys, but overall it wasn't too too bad. Crowd just seemed really out of it for some reason in this match. 5/10WWE CRUSERWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIPJaqueline (c) v. Chavo Guererro (arm tied behind his back)- Every now and then WWE creative has a brain fart and does something for now aparent reason. Jaqueline winning the cruserweight crown was one of them. Chavo was a great champ and had it completely soiled by this and then his father winning weeks later. The Division was really hurt by this.. Chavo wins thank god, but the division lost. 4/10United States ChampionshipJohn Cena (c) v. Renee Dupree- By far the match of the night up to this point. BUT, these two just don't have great chemistry. Dupree is loaded with talent, but he's still 21 years old and VERY VERY green. He just seems stiff. A good match by both although these two could probobly be capable of better. 6.5/10Booker T v. The Undertaker- good match. Lasted a little longer then it needed to, but a good match nonetheless. They really didn't develop this feud enough to make it interesting. I thought this match was solid from start to finish really. 7/10WWE ChampionshipEddie Guererro (c) v. John Bradshaw Layfield- BY FAR the match of the night. Now i'm not big on Bradshaw, but being a month into his title reign at the time i'm writing this review, he really knows how to work within himself and make his matches entertaining. The match is just an all out brawl from start to finish and the blood coming from eddie is incredible. He's cut so bad! They really told a great story and set up the rest of their feud quite well here. The crowd was really into it too. If someone tells you this match sucked, they didn't watch it, it was good no matter how much i can't stand bradshaw... 8.5/10Overall this ppv is a sure fire rental, but I'd hesitate to buy it. The WWE Championship match was by far the match of the night, althought there are some decent shows earlier in the production... Like I said, this is a decent rental.

reviewText: Judgement Day 2004 is a below average event.  Nothing really in general to say about the PPV other than the match card is pretty underwhelming with a couple exceptions.Rey Meysterio & Rob Van Dam vs. Dudley Boyz:This is one of three matches on the card that keeps this event from a complete failure.  Although with that said, it's nothing too original.  There is a lot of popular talent involved so that the match runs nicely with a lot of pace and fan involvement.  Overall a pretty good watch from four very reliable guys.Torrie Wilson vs. Dawn Marie:If Torrie loses the match, she's fired.  Needless to say it was the typical Smackdown diva match of its time that we've all come to know and love..Mordecai vs. Scotty 2 Hotty:Probably worse than the previous diva match if that's possible.  The PPV debut of Mordecai gives us a complete squash in less than five minutes.WWE Tag TitlesRico & Charlie Haas w/ Miss Jackie vs. Hardcore Holly & Billy Gunn:I guess at this point in WWE we were supposed to all have forgotten that Billy Gunn used to be on a team with Rico..whatever.  Anyway, this is one of those tag matches that you'll either love or hate.  I didn't mind it too much, aside from the usual antics of Rico (which went on a little too long this time around), there are a couple of nice spots and decent story telling with the match.  Haas in particular looks good here.  Give this one a look.Cruiserweight TitleJacqueline vs. Chavo Guerrero w/ Chavo Classic:I'm not going to defend this pointless match on any level.  It would have been one thing if they gave Jacqueline the belt, and at least gave her a semi-serious title reign, but that doesn't happen.  The match is stupid, short, and frustrating.  Chavo wins the belt back.United States TitleJohn Cena vs. Rene Dupree:This really really surprised me.  Both Cena AND Dupree look really good in this one.  The match isn't too long, but long enough to sell the story and produce a pretty good match.  Both men show some hints of technical mastery.  Aside from a couple of points where some bland submission holds are used to slow the pace down, this is actually probably the best match on the card.The Undertaker vs. Booker T:This is not one of the three matches I mentioned in the beginning of this review.  The storyline here was completely dumb and rushed.  You have Booker T for some reason bashing the Smackdown brand and somehow the Undertaker takes offense to that.  The match is completely one sided and I'm pretty darn sure we can all guess who wins.WWE TitleEddie Guerrero vs. JBL:This was one hell of a main event, and probably the only thing this PPV will ever be remembered for.  To start, we again had a stupid storyline that was rushed and untastefuly used (Eddie's mother has a heart attack).  Nonetheless, this match clocks in at a longer 25 minutes of hell, agony, and BLOOD.  It does a great job of putting over JBL's new character and showing Eddie as a great main eventer.  Starts off kind of slow and uneventful but boy does that turn around towards the end.  I'm sure some people might not like this type of match, but I certainly did.  Best main event of the year for me.Overall Judgement Day 2004 was free for all.  There were a couple of good tag matches, a good US Title match, and a main event that would merit the purchase of the event.

reviewText: <50: Ask for a refund for not only your money, but also your time. [F]50-54: Mediocre & disappointing. [D] (EG: Armageddon '03)55-59: Average. [C] (EG: Royal Rumble '04 & No Way Out '04)60-64: Worth A Watch. [C+] (EG: Backlash '04)65-69: Good event that was worth the money. [B] (EG: WrsetleMania 20)70-74: Very good. [B+] (EG: WrestleMania 19)75-79: Make sure you add this ppv to your video or dvd collection. [A] (EG: SummerSlam '02)80+ : Make sure that the video or dvd is locked in a safe & cannot be erased. Memorable. [A+]REY MYSTERIO & ROB VAN DAM defeated THE DUDLEY BOYZ: Obvious & good choice for the opener. Very solid 15 minute old-school tag-team match with The Dudleyz playing the bigger, cheating & double-teaming heels, while the faces seemed to always be in peril. Good move to have RVD wrestle the first 5 minutes, as the crowd was extremely hot for the eventual tag to Rey. I'm unsure if it was as wise to have Rey wrestle the next 7 minutes though, as only 1 tag by a team in 12 minutes makes it feel like you're almost watching a singles match to a degree. Some of the spots were too unnatural & choreographed for my liking, and while most people will think I'm talking about RVD, I'm actually talking about Rey. He was either not on the top of his game here, or the WWE are really misusing him. Probably the worst thing about the bout was that we knew the winner before the ending, as RVD's music started up halfway through the match!!! Solid, but flawed. Could have been a great deal better. Match Rating...7TORRIE WILSON defeated DAWN MARIE: Prior to this match, Kurt Angle came out & took an eternity to state that if Torrie lost, she would be fired. This started terribly bad!!! It was as sloppy as I have ever seen & both women seemed to be waiting for their opponent to do something, on more than one occasion. Thankfully, it got a little better. But not much more. Then it dragged out a little too long at 7 minutes. The only time the crowd got involved was when Dawn-Marie lost her pants. Match Rating...3MORDECAI defeated SCOTTY 2 HOTTY: This was the first time I've seen Mordecai, as we had his SmackDown promos edited out in Australia (for time reasons I think). A 4 minute squash match & an average one at that. Way too methodically paced & without any excitement at all. Luckily, nothing was really botched. More of an introduction to the character, than an actual match. Match Rating...4CHARLIE HAAS & RICO defeated HARDCORE HOLLY & BILLY GUNN to Retain the WWE Tag-Team Championship: Decent 10 minute tag match here. I thought Rico's shenanigans at the beginning of the bout went on too long & bogged the match down. But following that, we pretty much went to the match format of the opener, with Holly & Gunn playing the prototypical heel team decently (but not as good as The Dudleyz). Again (similar to the opener), Haas was dominated way too much for my liking. When Rico finally got the hot tag though, he did bring a lot of intensity to the bout, and the whole final 3 minutes or so were surprisingly very good. Match Rating...6CHAVO GUERRERO defeated JACQUELINE with One Arm tied behind his back to Win the WWE Cruiserweight Title: The stipulation in this bout was never going to mean it would be a classic (pardon the pun), but I suppose it wouldn't have been without the stipulation anyway. This 5 minute match was more for entertainment purposes than anything else. It moved along at a decent enough pace, and more importantly, it definitely increased Chavo's heel heat in my opinion. Chavo ended up winning easily when his arm was untied & Chavo Classic provided distraction after distraction to allow his son to hit a succession of moves to leave Jacqueline out for the count. Terrible as a wrestling match, but good in serving heat & (to a lesser extent) entertainment purposes. Match Rating...5JOHN CENA defeated RENE DUPREE to Retain the United States Title: I'm really torn on this 10 minute match. It was very flawed, but sort of entertaining as a whole. In fact (and this may sound harsh on Cena), the match sort of lived & died on Dupree. Cena was pretty much along for the ride (apart from getting his usual favorable crowd reaction). Dupree made quite a few inexperienced errors (especially early) which resulted in a fairly messy bout. There were also way too many restholds instigated by Dupree, which occasionally slowed the match to a maddening pace. But when the action was moving, there was good energy, intensity & crowd involvement. Both these guys have a huge future. Match Rating...6THE UNDERTAKER defeated BOOKER T: Ok match which had decent intensity. Psychology was tried for wrestling-wise, but pretty much failed. However, I really liked the way Booker T reacted to pretty much everything. Without knocking The Undertaker, I think this bout proved that Booker can still get it done in the ring on more than one level. In fact, I have to be honest & say that I was disappointed that he wasn't given the win here. Good crowd response, but the match was pretty much unspectacular. One rating point off for the bad booking, in that the silly supernatural crap in the feud had no relevance to the bout whatsoever. Match Rating...5JOHN BRADSHAW LAYFIELD defeated EDDIE GUERRERO by Disqualification in a Match for the WWE Championship: Very good intensity & crowd involvement in this main event. The enormous build-up given to this feud did help out the match & like I said last week, it was actually wise of the WWE to add more to the feud than simply an immigrant issue. Mostly a brawling match (which was to be expected), with pretty much no moments of fast-paced wrestling whatsoever. Eddie bladed way too much (a'la Vince McMahon at WrestleMania 19) & that did add to the psychology & intensity of the bout. It also provided a sufficient excuse for the slow pace & many restholds. Good duration at 23 minutes, with a disappointing DQ finish, that was luckily overcome by a further 5 minutes of hardcore intense action afterwards. Match Rating...7PPV RATING (43/80) = 54Looking at the key, I have basically given 'Judgment Day' a 'D' grade & said that it was 'mediocre & disappointing'. Well, mediocre it was, but it wasn't disappointing. In fact, due to the low expectations I had for the matches, I often found it hard not to rate them too lightly. I really did expect this card to fail. It passed pretty much because of an above-average main event & a solid opener. But even those 2 bouts were not standouts in any way, shape or form. Luckily, there were only 2 failing matches on the card (not surprisingly, they were the final 2 matches announced). In retrospect, it doesn't bother me that I ended up purchasing the ppv, but to those that didn't, you didn't miss much anyway.

reviewText: Filled with some DIRE matches, and only one good match (the Tag Team match), Judgment Day 2004 is a living tribute to the old 1998-2000 WCW PPVS of the past, which is'nt a good thing.1. RVD and Rey Mysterio vs The Dudley Boyz: Solid Tag Team effort from the two teams, the Dudleyz have become effective heels in the WWE, but RVD and Mysterio are WASTED in this match, why could'nt one of then have fought Eddie Guerrero rather than Bradshaw?2. Torrie Wilson vs Dawn Marie: Good for the XXX value of seeing Dawn's butt exposed, but nothing else.3. Mordecai vs Scotty 2 Hotty: Useless squash match which does'nt do either any favours, Mordecai has a great look, but wrestles like someone from 1993.4. WWE Tag Team Championships: Rico and Charlie Hass vs Billy Gunn and Hardcore Holly: If you've managed to stay awake so far, get ready to fall asleep, or realise you've died and gone to hell, boring match, Hardcore Holly has never deserved to be part of a PPV, Billy Gunn adds SOME credibility, as does Hass, but it falls apart with Rico, Holly, and the crappy Gay Jokes.5. WWE Cruserweight Championship: Chavo Guerrero vs Jaqelyn: If you have the DVD Remote control, press "Skip", because this match is nothing more than a hasty joke which sees Chavo reduced to fighting underserving females over a once credible championship.6. WWE UNITED STATES CHAMPIONSHIP: John Cena vs Reen Dupre: Not as bad as you'd expect, but it should have been given more time to properly develop, instead it feels rushed and appears to end FAR too early at the point where you might think this could turn into a great match7. Undertaker vs Booker T: Come on...we all know who wins here, 'Taker is broken down, and Booker needs a win to secure himself as a top heel, niether a good match or that oppertunity for Booker arises with this.8. WWE Championship: Eddie Guerrero vs John Bradshaw Leyfield: Arguably the worst WWE Main event since Undertaker vs Hulk Hogan at Judgment Day 2004, Eddie defends the WWE Champion against John Bradshaw Leyfeild in an unbelvibly boring match which is only saved by the credibile brawl the two have outside of the ring, J.B.L is'nt a good main eventer, but he has a good gimmick, and would be more effective feuding for the U.S Championship, Eddie proves why he is one of the finest in the buisness as he tries to carry J.B.L and partially succeeds.Overall, this is NOT a good PPV, and the only way I would recommend it to you is if a RAW match was part of the DVD extras.Avoid at all costs.
summary: Is it me, or is SMACKDOWN living in 1995?

reviewText: You would think coming off the high rating WrestleMania XX PPV & the just as great RAW Backlash PPV...you would think Judgment Day was gonna be right on the money.  Well, IT WASN'T.  All Judgment Day had was a good opener, two great main events, a nice title match and the rest of nothing more but a boring filler...even to the point where the crowd died & I fell asleep.  I didn't pay front row to fall asleep!  Anyways, I rented to the DVD to tape the four matches off of it.RVD/Rey Mysterio vs. Dudley Boyz - The Dudleyz recently turned heel & worked well with RVD & Mysterio.  Great opener.Torrie Wilson vs. Dawn Marie - Kurt Angle came out (he's General Manager at this time doing his wheelchair gimmick with Luther Reigns) and cut a good heel promo on L.A.  He then went on to blame Torrie Wilson for him getting hurt & put her a match against Dawn Marie.  The match was a dud.Mordecai vs. Scotty 2 Hotty - This was Mordecai's debut in a squash match against Scotty.  If you don't remember Mordecai then concider yourself lucky as he was gone in two months.Tag Team Champions Rico & Charlie Hass vs. Billy Gunn & Hardcore Holly - Eventhough Rico is good at the whole "I'm gay" gimmick...nobody gives a damn about Hardcore Holly & Billy Gunn (who were never on TV as a tag team until the week before) and Hass is a straight wrestler who couldn't save this match.  It just seemed like it dragged forever to the point where I think this is where I began to go to sleep.Crusierweight Champion Jacqueline vs. Chavo Guerrero - Jacqueline hadn't been seen on WWE TV to the point where people forgot she exsisted & then she comes out of nowhere & wins the title from Chavo?  Everyone knew that Chavo was gonna get the belt & I guess it was ment to be a comedy match but it just came off badly.  Was there a better way to give finger to the crusierweights than to just give Jacqueline the belt...oh I forgot, Chavo's dad won the belt later that week at the SmackDown taping & Funaki won it at the end of the year.U.S. Champion John Cena vs. Rene Dupree - Finally, the PPV starts to pick up here as Cean & Dupree for being in the business as long as they have been put together a great match.  People really got into this match as it was the best thing they've seen since the opening match.  Unfortunally, Dupree has been jobbing out ever since this match.Undertaker vs. Booker T - Taker just recently returned to his "dead man" gimmick while Booker T did a heel turn so this was fun to watch eventhough they did a dumb storyline leading up to it.  Like I said, fun match to watch.WWE Champion Eddie Guerrero (RIP) vs. J.B.L. - On the Eddie Guerrero tribute show, J.B.L. talked about how they almost had a riot when they wrestled in L.A...and he was telling the complete truth.  J.B.L. cut a promo earlier in the night & cut another one in the ring before the match that really got to the crowd to the point where I thought I was gonna see a riot because I never felt that much heat on a heel live.  This match was the best match on the card & that's saying something since J.B.L. only 2 months before hand was just a mid-card tag team wrestler.  Guerrero bleeds buckets here and is the best match in the entire Guerrero/J.B.L. fued.I don't remember all the DVD extras but I know they had the segments from the previous weeks SmackDown involving Booker T visiting a psychic & a graveyard; J.B.L. giving Eddie Guerrero's mom a heartattack & another J.B.L. promo with him kicking illegal immigrants out of Texas & back across the border; and a match from Heat.I don't recommend buying this at all...rent it if you can and watch the first match then skip to the last three because an hour of filler crap will put you to sleep at home.  Trust me because it put me to sleep when I was there live.
summary: I Saw This Live....AND IT WAS A WASTE OF MONEY!

reviewText: WWEJUDGMENT DAY 2004This was an event held by Smackdown back when the brands had separate PPV's, this one was good enough. The matches were good for the most part with some being not that great. The DVD as some good special features which is always a plus with me and it also makes me miss Sunday Night Heat. Over all I would say it was a good event but far from the best.1.REY MYSTERIO & RVD VS THE DUDLEY BOYZ-really good opening match with four of the best that has ever done it. This was a fun match with some high spots and that classic heel versus face feel to it. The Dudley's used their size advantage most of the match while the speed of Rey and RVD played well against the bigger guys. Good opening match and great choice for the slot, Rey and RVD take the win.Next we get Mr. Angle coming out and going off on L.A. and Eddie Guerrero but it was Torrie he was mainly after. He told her that if she lost her match she was fired.2.TORRIE WILSON VS DAWN MARIE-this was your typical Divas match with the heel controlling most of the match with Torrie coming back every once in a while. The best moment I am sure you remember is when Dawn loses her pants. Still Torrie gets the win and keeps her job.3.SCOTTY 2 HOTTY VS MORDECAI-this match was all about putting over the debuting Mordecai who you may remember better as Kevin Thorn from WWE's ECW. Any way he basically smashed Scotty in this squash match to make him look real dangerous.4.[WWE TAG TITLE]RICO & CHARLIE HAAS VS BILLY GUN & HARDCORE HOLLY-this was actually an enjoyable match with some good wrestling and some funny moments involving Rico. I think I actually miss him in the WWE. Good tag match but was more of the entertainment/funny match of the night. Haas and Rico keep the belts in a well paced match.5.[WWE CRUISERWEIGHT TITLE]JACQUELINE VS CHAVO GUERRERO-this match came about because Jacqueline had won the title from Chavo a few weeks earlier on Smackdown. The match was ok with Chavo having his hand tied behind his back. He eventually gets his hand free and dominates from there taking back the title.6.[US TITLE]JOHN CENA VS RENE DUPREE-this match was better than I was expecting it to be. Going back and watching it again I still feel the same way about it. Both guys look good here especially Dupree as he takes it to the fan favorite. Pretty much more of a brawling type match but it was good. Cena gets the win of course but it was a better match than I thought it would be.7.UNDERTAKER VS BOOKER T-now for some reason some people hated on this match but I liked it. I really enjoyed how Booker came across in this match and thought he performed very well. Sure the storyline going in was kinda crazy but Booker made it entertaining in my opinion. This was good match that Taker would end up winning.8.[WWE TITLE]EDDIE GUERRERO VS JBL-probably the best match on the card as not only Eddie delivered but so did JBL. Some people hate on him but I think he is underrated and his series with Eddie shows that. This match had a slower pace than I was expecting going in but it was a really good match. JBL used his size and power against the former cruiserweight but Eddie fought back with intensity. The crowd was really into this one and 100% behind Latino Heat, especially during the kick outs. Eddie gets cut real bad in this match which only added to the atmosphere of the match. Now regardless of how others felt I kinda liked the ending. JBL's sneaky way of getting the title in the ring to use backfires and Eddie uses it. Now this of course leads to a DQ but I thought it fit the story being told. Then of course the fight and beat down after the match that Eddie gives JBL made sure the feud would continue.BONUS MATCH9.FUNAKI VS MARK JIN-this was the match that was on Sunday Night Heat before the PPV. Funaki who will always be one of my favorites was facing Jindrak here in a quick little bout. This kinda was putting Jindrak over but Funaki looked good putting up some offense. Still it would be a loss for my boy and a win for Mark.This was a good DVD with some good special features like the match right above. But you also get moments from Sunday Night Heat, interviews and behind the scenes stuff. Also you get promos and some things leading into the matches. It also includes JBL hunting illegal immigrants, and Booker T and voodoo/graveyard.

reviewText: May 16, 2004 LA, CaliforniaJudgement Day is a pretty good Smackdown PPV with some good matches, some great matches and some DUD matches. This is going to be rated on a scale from 1 to 10 and I will also rate the extras.1. reviewText: Not the best performance by the Smackdown brand.  I was really tired while watching this one, but from what I can remember it wasnt' that good.1. Dudley's vs. Rey Mysterio & Rob Van DamGood way to kick off the show.  I actually think this was the best match of the night.  It got a little sloppy at times.  Mysterio and RVD make great partners.  (8/10)2. Torrie Wilson vs. Dawn MarieOnce again, who cares.  (1/10)3. Mordecai vs. Scotty 2 HottyThis was Mordecai's first match.  He has a good look, but was less than impressive in the match.  (4/10)4. Rico & Charlie Haas vs. Hardcore Holly & Billy Gunn (WWE Tag Team Titles)Pretty good match.  I think Holly and Gunn make a good team and should stay together to bring some credibility back to the tag team division.  Bit of a surprise ending.  (7.5/10)5. Chavo Guerrero vs. Jacqueline (Cruiserweight Title)Why?  They wasted a spot with this one.  Give another cruiserweight a shot.  Terrible story line.  (2/10)6. John Cena vs. Rene Dupree (U.S. Title)Nothing too great in this one.  Two young competitors with a good future, but didn't put on a good match.  (6/10)7. Undertaker vs. Booker TThese two had good beef going in, bu the match didn't live up to expectations.  Both guys looked to be off.  Not the best match, although the crowd did a good job to stay into it.  (7/10)8. Eddie Guerrero vs. JBL (WWE Championship)Kind of a slow match that really picks up at the end.  Very good heat coming in.  There are some good announce table bumps and close falls at the end.  There are some sick chair spots and lots of blood.  The end of the match and post match melee is the best part of the match.  It helps set up their match at the Great American Bash.  (7.5/10)I would not recommend anyone to pick up this DVD.  It was decent, but nothing too great happened.Overall Rating:  6.5/10

reviewText: 1.) RVD and Rey Mysterio vs The Dudley BoyzGreat, solid technical and athletic Tag Team match to open the show. RVD gets the pinfall over D-Von following a 5 Star Frog Splash. RVD and Mysterio were an awesome Tag Team and luckily we'd be seeing more of them on Smackdown in 2004.__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________2.) Torrie Wilson vs Dawn MarieThis was a filler match that was made after General Manager Kurt Angle called Torrie Wilson out and blamed her for the reason he was in a wheelchair. (Kurt Angle became Smackdown GM following Wrestlemania XX when Heyman"quit", got Chokeslammed off a ledge by Big Show not too long after after an altercation with Torrie, Show, and Angle and lead to Angle being in a wheelchair. A messy storyline altogether) So as punishment he put her match against Dawn Marie and made the stipulation that if Torrie lost, she'd be fired. Short and bland divas match. Smackdown wasn't necessarily known for having talented divas on their roster. The only noteworthy thing about this match was Dawn's attire malfunction where the back of her tights ripped open and exposed her bare butt. Torrie wins with a backslide pin and escapes to the back__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________We get a backstage segment from Bradshaw (who had recently rechristened himself as JBL) who cuts a great heel promo on Los Angeles and Latinos__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________3.) Scotty 2 Hotty vs MordecaiA pointless squash match that was used to get over this new Mordecai character. Unfortunately the Mordecai character turned out to be a total fail and Mordecai was released months later. He'd return years later on ECW known as Kevin Thorn__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________4.) WWE Tag Team Championship Match: Charlie Haas and Rico (c) w/Miss Jackie vs Hardcore Holly and Billy GunnMeh. Boring Tag Team match. No meaning to it. Miss Jackie is a nice view in the match though__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________5.) WWE Cruiserweight Championship Match: Chavo Guerrero w/Chavo Classic vs Jacqueline (c)This feud was rather a dumb one. It was interesting though to see Jacqueline with the Cruiserweight Championship. She was the only other diva, not counting the Hardcore Championship to hold a men's championship, with Chyna being the other woman who held the IC Championship. Chavo wrestled the match with one arm tied behind his back and cheats with the assistance of Chavo Classic to win the match. Chavo hits the Gory Bomb on Jacqueline to win the Cruiserweight Championship. This would be Jacqueline's last WWE appearance as she'd get released by WWE a few weeks later due to having no ideas on what to do with her. A shame really because a talented diva such as herself belonged on Raw where all the talent was at, rather than on Smackdown__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________6.) WWE United States Championship Match: Rene Dupree vs John Cena (c)This was a great solid match to watch. I was a big fan of Rene Dupree and loved his French gimmick. Ultimately this feud was the typical, outdated 1980s anti-American vs American feud but the match was great that gets a fair amount of time for Cena and Dupree to have their match. John Cena ends up retaining the title with a FU on Dupree. Great match. It's disappointing that WWE misused Dupree. He could've been a great asset to the company__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________7.) Booker T vs The Undertaker w/Paul BearerNot too bad of a match. The reason for it happening was....so-so but Booker and Taker give a decent showing here. Undertaker wins with the Tombstone Piledriver__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________8.) WWE Championship Match: JBL vs Eddie GuerreroWhat a great main event match this was. Eddie and JBL go at it with a lot of personal riding on the match after JBL gave Eddie's mother a heart attack during a house show. The feud was great and the match told the story. This match however is less known for the action and more remembered for the horrific blade job Eddie did in the match following a sick chair shot from JBL. His blood gushed on the floor, the announce table and stained the ring. This was one of the few times where a match in WWE surpassed the classification of bloody and would suit the lines of gory. I mean Eddie looked like he had just came out of a Texas Chainsaw or Saw movie as his face was nearly painted in his own blood as it flowed into his eyes and wetted his hair and flows down his body. This gory match ends on a DQ after Eddie nails JBL with the WWE Championship.Overall: Not a bad PPV. I feel Smackdown lacked a lot of proper booking in early-mid 2004 as a lot of their PPVs early on featured a lot of pointless and boring filler/jobber matches. Aside from the 2 or 3 pointless or boring matches, Judgment Day 2004 passes as a watchable PPV. Obviously Eddie vs JBL was the match of the night
summary: Not A Bad PPV; Eddie vs JBL Steals The Show

reviewText: I have been a wrestling fan since 1996 and have watched all kinds of wrestling. I have a wrestling DVD/VHS collection spanning over 50 all together. This is the most complete and accurate review of this VHS you will find. I hope you find this review helpful; remember to vote helpful or not helpful. (Note-Each VHS I review has a "Match of the VHS" award somewhere in it.)WWE-Judgment Day 2004Judgment Day 2004 wasn't a good PPV at all. Most of the matches are poor. The only real reason to buy this would be the bloodbath between JBL and Eddie Guerrero. The extras are pretty nice as well and include a Heat match and a hilarious JBL promo where he runs illegals out of the country.Dudley Boyz VS Rey Mysterio & Rob Van DamThis is a solid tag team match. The Dudleys control most of the match with quick tags. Mysterio and RVD hit some good highflying moves toward the end of the match. That includes a double 619 and a Lifting Frakensteiner.RATING- 6.5/10After this match, General Manager Kurt Angle comes out and announces that if Torrie wins the next match, she will be fired.If Torrie Loses, She is FiredDawn Marie VS Torrie WilsonThese two have fought so many times on PPV it's ridiculous. This match is a mess with a few good moments thrown in the mix. They seem to stumble into the moves they do. Dawn hits a good leg drop on Torrie while they are on the outside. Dawn has a wardrobe malfunction that I'm sure many will love.RATING- 5/10Mordecai VS Scotty 2 HottyThis was just a squash match. However, this is one of my favorite squash matches. Scotty gets destroyed. Mordecai had so much potential.RATING- 7/10WWE Tag Team ChampionshipCharlie Haas & Rico(c) VS Billy Gunn & Hardcore HollyThis was a fun match with Rico using his sexual orientation to fix advantage. Nothing much past Rico acting very funny and scaring everyone.RATING- 6.5/10Chavo has one hand tied behind his backWWE Cruiserweight ChampionshipJacqueline(c) VS Chavo Guerrero w/Chavo ClassicOkay, this is stupid. Chavo Classic gets involved and Chavo uses both hands anyway.RATING- 1/10United States ChampionshipJohn Cena(c) VS Rene DupreeThis was a solid match up with a good build up. The match goes back and forth with some good action. The ending is very good.RATING- 7.5/10Booker T VS UndertakerUndertaker really dominates most of this match with Booker getting some flurries here and there. The storyline was that Booker had voodoo on his side. Still, you known that Undertaker is going to win.RATING- 7/10WWE ChampionshipEddie Guerrero(c) VS John Bradshaw LayfieldJBL had caused Eddie's mother to have a heart attack at a recent house show. Eddie begins the assault on JBL early on. JBL is beat on for a while until he reverses a Irish whip into the steel steps. There is some more brawling after that. Eddie takes a sick chair shot that busts him open. He bleeds dangerous amounts of blood for the rest of the match. I liked the ending and thought it helped fuel the feud.RATING- 9/10

reviewText: I just watched Judgment Day 2004 and I have to say it is one of my favorite ppv's ever, and I didn't even buy it when it was on ppv.  The whole card is really solid, and I know it sounds crazy, but one of the biggest surpises is the Torrie/Dawn Marie match.  They really had a good match, and are both GORGEOUS.  The opening tag team match with the Dudleys is REALLY good.  The Cena match is also above average.  Now, the Eddie/JBL match is AMAZING and one of the greatest matches of all time.  Absolutley BRUTAL and Eddie gave one of the great performances EVER.  JBL may be one of the greatest heels ever...up there with HHH....he's that good....Just watch his promo before the match....I forgot how good JBL really was and sadly I didn't appreciate him at the time....JBL also wrestled great and the chair shots were the worst I have ever seen, especially the one Eddie took.  As much as I watched it, every time Eddie took that chair shot I cringed.  I can't believe how much blood he lost, and was still able to wrestle...Eddie's performance may be the most courageous performance in a ring EVER, and that's not even exaggerating....in actuality the match should have been stopped and Eddie taken to the back.  As it turned out, however, we got one of the all-time greatest matches.  This DVD is MUST-OWN.  You get to see Eddie and JBL at their absolute best, and....WRESTLING at its absolute best!!!
summary: Must own dvd for any wrestling video library!!!

reviewText: This ppv had a few good matches but nothing special. GAB was way better and would have been way better if not for the main event it should have been mid card and Eddie vs. JBL should have got the main event. RVD/Mysterio vs. Dudley Boyz was the best opener to a ppv this year, Cena vs. Dupree started off great but was too short. If this match had another 7-10 minutes it would have been great. JBL vs. Eddie Guerrero was the other good match. Everyone who hates JBL has got to admit he did a great job in this match and Eddie did good too. This was a slobber knocker all the way through and would have been better no disq. The ending was the only bad part, Why did it end with a Disqualification. Their match at the great American Bash was better and their cage match on SD this week was even better it was awsome. Yes, Kurt Angle can return to the ring and help the wwe.The mid card was a let down and is the reason everyone is giving this ppv low ratings. Come on, Chavo vs. Jackie,Torrie vs. Dawn Marie, Mordecai vs. Scotty 2 hotty and the horrible tag title match. I like Mordecai and his character is awsome but why is he wrestling guys like Scotty in 3 minute matches. too bad Mordecai has to leave the wwe, I don't know why they have to do that. Oh yeah, I forgot about Booker T vs. The Undertaker. It was pretty slow paced and an average match. Undertaker can do way better and so can Booker. I expected this to be one of the best matches but it wasn't. Overall a disappointing SD ppv. Why can't Vince and the WWE just make a card that go's a bit like this. It would sky rocket ratings.Cruiserweight title-Rey Mysterio vs. Billy KidmanU.S Title-John Cena vs. RVD vs. Mordecai vs. Kenzo Suzukiwwe tag team titles-Dudley boyz vs Dupree/Booker TWWE Title-JBL vs. Eddie Guerrero vs. Kurt Angle vs. Undertaker vs. Rikishi vs. Big Show  in an Elimination Chamber matchPlus some rival matches for the mid card.Now that would be great but it would never happen.

reviewText: This ppv wasn't great but was alot better than some people say it was. The 3 main events were decent and the opener was spectacular but the mid card let this ppv down. Here is how I rate the matches.RATING SCALE40- bad ppv40-50 okay ppv50-60 average ppv60-70 good ppv70-80 exellent ppv80+ classic ppvMysterio/RVD def. The Dudley Boyz  Time-15 minutes 9/10probably match of the night and the best tag match I have seen in a while. It had everything from high flying moves to quick counters and near falls. The team of Mysterio/RVD is an exciting combination and they are going to make an exhilarating team. Hopefully they will get the tag title before or at Wrestlemania 21. In the end Mysterio and RVD pick up the win with a bang.Torrie vs. Dawn Marie  TIME-7 minutes 4/10Actually better than I thought it would be but still 2nd worst match of the night, I liked this better than Scotty vs. Mordecai. Torrie Wilson keeps her job after getting the three count at the 7 minute mark.Mordecai vs. Scotty 2 Hotty  TIME-4 minutes 3/10WHAT THE HELL IS THIS CRAP. These are the sort of matches that bring WWE down. Why should Mordecai debut in a 3-4 minute squash match at a ppv. Anyway Mordecai wins with the cruserfyer in an inimpressive debut.WWE Tag Team TitlesCharlie Haas/Rico vs. Holly/Gunn  TIME-10 minutes 6/10Actually a pretty good match. It was more of a comedy show than a wrestling match but was entertaining and got the crowd going. I don't know why Haas isn't a singles wrestler, he is a great talent and should be put into the U.S Title picture. Haas and Rico retain the titles after a funny ending.Cruiserweight TitleJackie vs. Chavo Guerrero  TIME-6 minutes 5/10BAD to say the least. Chavo is a great wrestler but this is just a joke putting him in this match. Chavo wins the title again anyway after Chavo senoir untied his hand and he hit his finisher.U.S ChampionshipJohn Cena vs. Renee Dupree  TIME-11 minutes 7.5/10A very decent match up between two of Smackdowns young studs. I like Dupree and he deserves to be a singles wrestler but Cena is not a good wrestler at all. He is dull and boring to watch and needs to be carried in every match he's in. Both men did a great job here thought producing lots of exciting action and counters. I wanted Dupree to win but Cena hits the F.U to retain the championship.Booker T vs. The Undertaker  TIME-11 minutes 7/10I expected alot better but I guess that was to much to ask. Stll decent but had a good build up and should have delivered. Undertaker isn't that good and should retire soon giving younger talents some time. As expected Taker wins with the chokeslam/Tombstone piledriver combination.WWE ChampionshipEddie Guerrero vs. John Bradshaw Layfield  TIME-23 minutes 8.5/10An all out brawl, Not much wrestling here folks. JBL did a good job in this match as did Eddie. The few highlights were Eddie getting absoulutly smashed with the chair, JBL getting hit with the steps,chair and belt and the beating afterwards. Eddie Guerrero gets disqualified after the ref saw him use the belt on JBL.Overall Judgement day was okay and scored 50/80. RATING SCALE-62 which means it was average.

reviewText: This is Mudd.  This PPV was possibly the worst I have ever ordered.  It has slow and boring matches that are painful to watch.Rob Van Dam & Rey Mysterio vs. Dudley Boys was a good opener that featured high-flying action and finally RVD & Mysterio pull out the win over the Dudley Boys. (7.5/10)Torrie Wilson vs. Dawn Marie was a match that had to get some divas on the PPV some how and it was not even an official match.  It wasn't made until Judgment Day itself.  Torrie Wilson won the match over Dawn and it was just crap. (1/10)Charlie Haas & Rico vs. Billy Gunn & Hardcore Holly for the WWE Tag Team Championship.  This was a boring bout until Haas really started to put on a show and Rico & Charlie retain the belts in a rivalry that came out of nowhere. (6/10)Mordecai vs. Scotty 2 Hotty was a squash match and I believe that Mordecai could have had a challenging opponent bucause he nearly kills Scotty.  I wish Scotty would come back.  Mordecai wins and don't waist time on this garbage.  (4/10)Chavo Guerrero vs. Jacqueline for the Cruiserweight Championship.  This match couldn't have been any worse then it was but it was just to get Chavo the gold back and Jacqueline never should have won in the first place. (2.5/10)John Cena vs. Rene Dupree for the United States Championship.  This was about the same as the opener but this was pound & ground stlye action.  There was no way that Rene was gonna win the title so obviously Cena retained. (7.5/10)Undertaker vs. Booker T had some great buid-up and I thought it was good in the end but not really that good and its a little creepy with Booker having to go to the Graveyard to get dirt and then a hand sticking out.  Anyway Taker beats Booker with the Chokeslam/Tombstone combition. (7.5/10)Eddie Guerrero vs. JBL for the WWE Championship.  This somehow is match of the night and if you think Taker bleed bad at No Mercy 2002 then you need to see this Eddie bleeds 3 times as much if you can believe it.  JBL won the match by DQ but I don't like the PPV ending in a DQ.  Eddie is still champ but he loses it at the Great American Bash. (8/10)Overall this PPV was pretty bad but it's not the worst of 2004 that honor goes to the Royal Rumble which was bad as well.  Don't get this DVD unless for the Main Event then you have to get The Great American Bash.

reviewText: John Bradshaw Layfield guaranteed a victory over Eddie Guerrero at Judgment Day, and he lived up to his word.  However, JBL's win came at a cost.  Layfield beat Guerrero by disqualification after Guerrero hit JBL with the WWE Championship.  Latino Heat then unleashed a savage assualt on JBL.  JBL won the battle, but by the time the evening ended it appeared that Guerrero won the war.

reviewText: Judgment Day 2004Rob Van Dam & Rey Mysterio V Dudley BoysAn ok opener, but nothing you can't see on Smackdown. All these guys can do way better. 6/10Torrie Wilson V Dawn MarieNot only has this match already been on at least 2 PPVs before, but it is just crap. 1 less point for it being on PPV twice already. 2/10Mordecai V Scotty 2 HottyI was interested to see Mordecai debut, but the match was very short and it was just a very quick squash match. 5/10WWE Tag Team ChampionshipCharlie Haas & Rico V Billy Gunn & Hardcore HollyAn ok tag-team match here, but nothing amazing. I think Rico is holding back Haas. 6/10WWE Cruiserweight ChampionshipChavo Guerrero V JacquelineWhat in the hell is this? A joke?! Putting a talented wrestler like Chavo against a crap woman wrestler is just insulting. It is an insult to Chavo and an insult to the Cruiserweight title. 2/10United States ChampionshipJohn Cena V Rene DupreeTwo good wrestlers go at it one on one, but nothing very spectacular happens. 7/10Undertaker V Booker TA pretty good match here. Booker uses some dirt in Taker's eyes but it doesn't help much. Taker wins with a chokeslam and tombstone. It could have been better, but it was quite good. 7/10WWE ChampionshipEddie Guerrero V JBLThis was actually the best match of the night I think, it was pretty decent. However it's not to main-event standard. JBL just isn't good enough to be in main-events (although Eddie is). Whilst the match was all right, it's kind of stupid that it ends in DQ. Also, Eddie bleeds way too much, and it kind of looks stupid really. I wouldn't mind if they actually used lots of weapons, but Eddie bleeds like crazy from just 1 chair shot. I'm glad JBL didn't win the title, and I hope he doesn't because he just isn't good enough for it. He should go for the US title instead. Overall a decent match, but should have been better since it was the main event. 7/10OverallBetter than I expected, but still not very good. The last 3 matches were fairly decent, but everything else varied from average to awful. Smackdown PPVs are never as good as Raw PPVs or Both-brand PPVs and this proves it.

matches on PPV's since 2002 or so.Neither can wrestle so either get rid of them or send them to raw with wrestling diva's for experience.My rating 0/10.Match Three-Mordecai Vs Scotty 2 Hotty-This match was to debut the white undertaker Mordecai.What better way to make Mordecai look strong then to absolutely squash Scotty in three minutes.Wasted just over a month ago Scotty was a tag team champion,now he's back to jobbing for people.This is what judgement day is about beating people mercisley and Mordecai did that.My rating 4/10.Match Four-Tag Team Championship-Rico&Charlie; Haas(C) Vs Hardcore Holly.This match between the team which makes each other sick and the men who have been around forever with nothing to do.Good back and forth match.The ending was a little bit of a finisher fest but still a good match making up for the last two none the less.My rating 6/10.Match Five-Cruiserweight Championship-Jacqueline(C)Vs Chavo Guerrero.This match had the stupid stipulation of Chavo has one hand tied behind his back.Two weeks earlier on Smackdown Jacqueline accepted Chavo's open challenge and she beat him to only have to do a rematch against him again.This was a average match chokeslams then sets up and hits the tombstone on Book for the 1,2,3.This a great setup for the main event.My rating 7.5/10.Match Eight-Main Event-WWE Championship-Eddie Guerrero(C)Vs JBL.The recent change of look and heel turn by JBL has been quite good.They need more good heels cause at this time there was only HHH,Angle who were main event heels.The match is a good time bout twenty mintutes with noone winning cleanly setting up there rematch.This is what Judgement days about.Bloody competitors nailing each other all over the arena.Eddie gets busted open badly during the match.Then after the match Eddie beats the holy hell out of JBL busting him open really bad.My rating 8.5/10.This show received 56.25% which is equivalent to a C+.This was a good show.Just the bad match with the womens and every other match was good.This a good sign for Smackdown with two good PPV's this year.
